1
00:00:00,131 --> 00:00:01,552
(This drama complied with production
guidelines for filming child actors,)

2
00:00:01,576 --> 00:00:03,013
(and some scenes used
generative AI technology.)

3
00:00:03,572 --> 00:00:05,869
(Episode 8)

4
00:00:12,216 --> 00:00:14,557
Sa Bin, thank you for coming.

5
00:00:14,770 --> 00:00:16,040
Of course I'd come.

6
00:00:16,821 --> 00:00:19,870
- I thought I'd see him once he recovered.
- Right.

7
00:00:20,355 --> 00:00:23,987
He talked about you a lot too.
He said we should have a drink sometime.

8
00:00:24,849 --> 00:00:26,756
Let's go have a meal together.

9
00:00:38,675 --> 00:00:41,936
(Boyak Oriental Medicine Clinic)

10
00:00:42,420 --> 00:00:44,172
"Boyak?"

11
00:01:17,876 --> 00:01:19,484
Thanks for coming.

12
00:01:30,475 --> 00:01:32,373
People from Seung Woo's company came,

13
00:01:32,615 --> 00:01:34,307
but why didn't anyone from yours?

14
00:01:35,787 --> 00:01:37,338
I didn't tell anyone.

15
00:01:38,470 --> 00:01:39,719
I just took the day off.

16
00:01:41,763 --> 00:01:45,529
It would've been strange
to suddenly tell them my dad died.

17
00:01:55,963 --> 00:01:58,309
Your mom's hurt.

18
00:01:58,683 --> 00:02:00,429
I told you to let them know.

19
00:02:00,772 --> 00:02:02,930
You said you were more than just a son.
So what is this?

20
00:02:02,931 --> 00:02:04,498
Be quiet.

21
00:02:05,997 --> 00:02:09,263
Don't grow up to be like your dad, okay?

22
00:02:09,265 --> 00:02:11,031
I'm gonna punish you.

23
00:02:11,913 --> 00:02:14,815
You're adorable. You're my son.

24
00:02:16,390 --> 00:02:18,552
- Take care, Aunt.
- Goodbye.

25
00:02:18,554 --> 00:02:19,657
Okay.

26
00:02:28,237 --> 00:02:30,435
- Welcome. Please come in.
- Hello.

27
00:02:50,275 --> 00:02:51,449
What's your problem?

28
00:02:51,450 --> 00:02:52,622
Happy now?

29
00:02:52,995 --> 00:02:55,662
Happy making her suffer over those papers?

30
00:02:55,664 --> 00:02:59,210
How do you sleep at night
after making her live like that?

31
00:02:59,212 --> 00:03:00,807
I never told her to.

32
00:03:00,808 --> 00:03:02,366
So that's your answer?

33
00:03:03,178 --> 00:03:04,633
I won't say she did the right thing.

34
00:03:04,634 --> 00:03:07,214
Then leave it at that.

35
00:03:07,216 --> 00:03:09,293
- What else is there to...
- You're a woman too.

36
00:03:09,294 --> 00:03:10,779
You've loved someone too.

37
00:03:10,781 --> 00:03:14,561
Yet you made a woman living under her own name
live in fear…

38
00:03:14,563 --> 00:03:16,513
Does that make you happy?

39
00:03:16,515 --> 00:03:18,290
I've always wondered about that.

40
00:03:18,292 --> 00:03:20,559
Grandmother, what are you doing?

41
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:24,033
You even drove a young girl
to the point of cutting her wrists,

42
00:03:24,034 --> 00:03:25,936
and you didn't even flinch?

43
00:03:26,355 --> 00:03:28,081
That's no way to live.

44
00:03:28,083 --> 00:03:30,822
Sometimes relationships fall apart.
Do you have to take revenge like this?

45
00:03:30,824 --> 00:03:33,779
You should live with a good heart
for your child's sake.

46
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:35,293
It felt good.

47
00:03:35,295 --> 00:03:37,944
I'm glad I held out until the end.

48
00:03:38,770 --> 00:03:43,033
But I'll take your words to heart.
I'll be leaving now.

49
00:03:43,035 --> 00:03:45,390
I'd heard she was ruthless,

50
00:03:45,392 --> 00:03:47,826
but now I understand why your father
met such an untimely death.

51
00:03:56,787 --> 00:03:59,054
Grandmother, why did you do that?

52
00:04:29,211 --> 00:04:30,773
I'm sorry.

53
00:04:32,136 --> 00:04:33,690
Why are you sorry?

54
00:04:33,692 --> 00:04:36,469
I didn't know
she'd suddenly act like that.

55
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:39,360
I'm sorry.

56
00:05:00,493 --> 00:05:01,711
Mom.

57
00:05:01,712 --> 00:05:05,803
Mother, just hold on a little longer.

58
00:05:06,451 --> 00:05:09,829
I've put up with this for 20 years.
I'm sick of it.

59
00:05:10,369 --> 00:05:13,482
Merge with them.
Admit we lost and say we'll merge.

60
00:05:13,484 --> 00:05:16,766
When Seung Woo's guests
and relatives arrive, greet them with him.

61
00:05:16,768 --> 00:05:19,688
You said no one from your side would come.
You go to the crematorium tomorrow.

62
00:05:19,690 --> 00:05:21,679
You prepared the documents, right?

63
00:05:21,681 --> 00:05:24,564
Let's finish this and be done with it.
I'm sick of it.

64
00:05:33,014 --> 00:05:35,082
(Haemyeong University Hospital,
Funeral Hall)

65
00:05:35,172 --> 00:05:36,642
One, two, three!

66
00:05:37,964 --> 00:05:40,455
- We have to throw the same one.
- One, two, three.

67
00:05:47,969 --> 00:05:49,886
One, two, three!

68
00:06:08,385 --> 00:06:10,771
- What?
- The funeral procession is tomorrow.

69
00:06:10,773 --> 00:06:13,227
- If we're going, we have to go now.
- Are you crazy? Why would we go?

70
00:06:13,229 --> 00:06:14,789
He's your brother-in-law.

71
00:06:14,790 --> 00:06:16,720
"Brother-in-law?"
To someone who doesn't even have a sister?

72
00:06:16,722 --> 00:06:18,239
- Be quiet.
- Honey.

73
00:06:18,241 --> 00:06:20,015
Good riddance. What a waste.

74
00:06:20,016 --> 00:06:21,405
I should've killed him myself.

75
00:06:21,407 --> 00:06:24,842
Don't say that.
I heard Yeong Ju was there when he died.

76
00:06:25,923 --> 00:06:30,061
- A fool stays a fool forever.
- It was cancer. Pancreatic cancer.

77
00:06:30,063 --> 00:06:31,826
He didn't even last two months
after being diagnosed.

78
00:06:31,853 --> 00:06:33,067
That's unfortunate.

79
00:06:33,069 --> 00:06:35,280
He should've suffered terribly
for a long time before dying.

80
00:06:35,281 --> 00:06:36,426
But...

81
00:06:37,161 --> 00:06:39,543
I heard that woman set up
another funeral room right next to his.

82
00:06:39,544 --> 00:06:41,329
She has more guests coming.

83
00:06:43,540 --> 00:06:45,586
That idiot. She keeps letting
people walk all over her.

84
00:06:45,587 --> 00:06:46,689
Let's go.

85
00:06:46,842 --> 00:06:47,982
Yes.

86
00:06:50,361 --> 00:06:53,882
It's the same hospital.
Go comfort your sister while you're there.

87
00:06:53,884 --> 00:06:55,600
I told you, I don't have a sister.

88
00:07:05,805 --> 00:07:06,959
Dad.

89
00:07:09,350 --> 00:07:10,609
A lot of people came, right?

90
00:07:10,775 --> 00:07:12,329
They say many people came earlier today.

91
00:07:12,807 --> 00:07:15,787
Security is tight
because the President might come tonight.

92
00:07:15,814 --> 00:07:18,206
- The Minister of Culture already came.
- What about Do Hee?

93
00:07:18,208 --> 00:07:19,501
She's parking now.

94
00:07:19,690 --> 00:07:21,101
Let's head down first.

95
00:07:29,638 --> 00:07:30,998
(Room 1, Cha Min Ki, Spouse, No Yeong Ju)

96
00:07:31,370 --> 00:07:33,158
It's Na Ji Ni's dad.

97
00:07:33,160 --> 00:07:35,358
(Room 1, Cha Min Ki, Spouse, No Yeong Ju,
Sons, Cha Seung Hyun, Cha Seung Woo)

98
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:37,367
(VIP Room 1, Cha Min Ki,
Spouse, Na Se Ri, Daughter, Na Ji Ni)

99
00:07:39,386 --> 00:07:42,253
No way. My goodness.

100
00:07:51,512 --> 00:07:52,832
Ma'am.

101
00:07:57,051 --> 00:08:00,639
Don't you recognize me?
I'm Do Hee, Ji Ni's friend.

102
00:08:05,377 --> 00:08:06,694
Of course I do.

103
00:08:07,675 --> 00:08:10,697
How could I forget you?
Even in my dreams, I can't forget.

104
00:08:10,724 --> 00:08:14,044
- Why so intense?
- Why are you here?

105
00:08:14,045 --> 00:08:15,684
How dare you show your face?

106
00:08:15,686 --> 00:08:19,064
Get out before Ji Ni's dad rises
from his coffin!

107
00:08:19,066 --> 00:08:21,497
Why are you saying such scary things?

108
00:08:21,741 --> 00:08:24,696
The minister passed away, so I came
to pay respects on behalf of my parents,

109
00:08:24,725 --> 00:08:26,862
and given our history, I stopped by.

110
00:08:27,784 --> 00:08:30,099
- That's harsh.
- Get out!

111
00:08:30,465 --> 00:08:32,652
I can't stand your face.

112
00:08:32,653 --> 00:08:35,675
Who kept Ji Ni
from even going to high school?

113
00:08:36,135 --> 00:08:40,283
That wasn't me. She didn't go
because she was ashamed of her parents.

114
00:08:41,146 --> 00:08:42,640
But, Ma'am,

115
00:08:43,181 --> 00:08:46,195
it looks like you're still not
his legal wife.

116
00:08:46,646 --> 00:08:49,945
- What did you say, you...
- At someone else's funeral,

117
00:08:51,155 --> 00:08:53,421
please watch your behavior.

118
00:09:00,622 --> 00:09:06,008
- Get out. Leave now!
- You don't have to tell me. I'm leaving.

119
00:09:07,587 --> 00:09:10,061
May you rest in peace.

120
00:09:10,694 --> 00:09:13,222
I always wished I had a dad like you.

121
00:09:13,875 --> 00:09:15,383
You little...

122
00:09:17,210 --> 00:09:19,506
Want to suffer at my father's hands again?

123
00:09:19,797 --> 00:09:22,047
See you next time, Ma'am.

124
00:09:28,447 --> 00:09:33,091
It's because you took over the room
but left the display unchanged!

125
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:42,041
Honey,

126
00:09:42,721 --> 00:09:48,342
the girl who nearly drove Ji Ni to death
came here to rub salt in the wound,

127
00:09:48,344 --> 00:09:50,664
and what are you doing?

128
00:09:50,665 --> 00:09:53,394
You should protect us!

129
00:09:57,260 --> 00:09:59,790
Jung A.

130
00:09:59,827 --> 00:10:01,646
This is breaking my heart.

131
00:10:02,421 --> 00:10:04,913
It's killing me.

132
00:10:06,209 --> 00:10:07,647
My goodness.

133
00:10:16,601 --> 00:10:18,332
Please hang in there a little longer.

134
00:10:19,022 --> 00:10:20,518
Once we leave tomorrow,

135
00:10:20,883 --> 00:10:22,791
it'll really all be over.

136
00:10:25,506 --> 00:10:28,146
This is breaking my heart.

137
00:10:47,621 --> 00:10:49,187
Ji Ni.

138
00:10:49,665 --> 00:10:52,314
- O Reum, you're here?
- Yes!

139
00:10:52,464 --> 00:10:53,787
O Reum!

140
00:10:55,213 --> 00:10:57,616
It's hot. Why aren't you going inside?

141
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:00,037
I just felt a bit suffocated.

142
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:03,449
Then could you watch O Reum for a bit?

143
00:11:03,593 --> 00:11:06,610
I have something to take care of
with a friend here at the hospital.

144
00:11:06,660 --> 00:11:07,876
I'll be back soon.

145
00:11:07,950 --> 00:11:09,311
Yes, sure.

146
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:10,858
If he cries, take him inside.

147
00:11:10,883 --> 00:11:12,299
His dad's there.

148
00:11:12,495 --> 00:11:13,592
Okay.

149
00:11:18,686 --> 00:11:21,679
- Want to play with me?
- Yes! Let's draw!

150
00:11:21,703 --> 00:11:23,619
Want to draw together?

151
00:11:24,132 --> 00:11:26,959
- Want to play with this?
- Yes.

152
00:11:28,629 --> 00:11:30,500
Let's take a look.

153
00:11:34,853 --> 00:11:35,853
Really?

154
00:12:19,486 --> 00:12:20,667
Ji Hu, what are you doing?

155
00:12:20,924 --> 00:12:21,924
Let's go.

156
00:12:22,357 --> 00:12:23,357
Okay.

157
00:12:25,032 --> 00:12:26,697
What are you looking at?

158
00:12:29,792 --> 00:12:31,213
I said let's go!

159
00:12:47,346 --> 00:12:49,429
The pretty girl is here!

160
00:12:49,454 --> 00:12:51,791
- Hurry!
- Where is she?

161
00:12:52,173 --> 00:12:53,749
- I'm second, right?
- Let's go!

162
00:12:53,773 --> 00:12:56,542
The pretty girl showed up!

163
00:13:01,006 --> 00:13:02,006
(Im Ji Hu)

164
00:13:08,659 --> 00:13:10,253
Hey, Im Ji Hu, hurry!

165
00:13:11,706 --> 00:13:13,273
Sorry, you've got a competition, right?

166
00:13:13,312 --> 00:13:14,539
Even if I didn't,

167
00:13:14,620 --> 00:13:16,813
I told you not to barge in like that!

168
00:13:16,838 --> 00:13:18,333
You're so sensitive.

169
00:13:18,735 --> 00:13:20,213
Did you really think I'd go?

170
00:13:21,146 --> 00:13:23,532
Come on, let's go. Take a break.

171
00:13:23,586 --> 00:13:25,247
They say a gorgeous girl just transferred
to middle school.

172
00:13:25,273 --> 00:13:26,812
Everyone's running to see her.

173
00:13:26,837 --> 00:13:28,521
She's just a middle schooler.
How pretty can she be?

174
00:13:28,548 --> 00:13:30,138
You think high schoolers
would rush over for that?

175
00:13:30,163 --> 00:13:32,664
Ji Hu, don't we need something
to live for?

176
00:13:32,747 --> 00:13:34,106
<i>No no no no</i>

177
00:13:34,159 --> 00:13:36,353
They say more volunteered to be spies
for North Korea to see Girls' Generation.

178
00:13:36,379 --> 00:13:38,993
And now a beauty shows up at school.

179
00:13:40,153 --> 00:13:41,565
But we don't even know her name.

180
00:13:43,021 --> 00:13:46,000
- What did I expect from you guys?
- Anyway, they say she's pretty. Cute too.

181
00:13:46,025 --> 00:13:47,131
And she's good at drawing.

182
00:13:47,133 --> 00:13:48,657
The art club's going crazy right now.

183
00:13:48,682 --> 00:13:50,370
Let's go!

184
00:13:54,448 --> 00:13:56,168
Okay.

185
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,883
You go be Beethoven.

186
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:06,146
- Who is she?
- Hey, over here!

187
00:14:06,171 --> 00:14:08,006
Why is she so pretty?

188
00:14:08,031 --> 00:14:09,676
Hey, she goes to our school too.

189
00:14:09,685 --> 00:14:11,620
What class is she in?

190
00:14:13,711 --> 00:14:16,691
If you become an idol, remember me!

191
00:14:16,727 --> 00:14:18,155
- What grade are you in?
- What grade and class are you in?

192
00:14:18,179 --> 00:14:20,172
Hey, give me an autograph!

193
00:14:20,928 --> 00:14:23,980
Don't forget me when you become an idol!

194
00:14:30,703 --> 00:14:32,145
(Na Ji Ni)

195
00:14:33,993 --> 00:14:35,040
(Im Ji Hu)

196
00:14:44,207 --> 00:14:45,595
They must've had a fight, right?

197
00:14:45,973 --> 00:14:47,806
Do Hee seems nervous around him.

198
00:14:48,138 --> 00:14:49,257
Right.

199
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:51,619
Why would he fight with Do Hee?

200
00:14:51,668 --> 00:14:53,954
She's charming, perceptive, and perfect.

201
00:14:54,432 --> 00:14:55,969
He doesn't know how lucky he is.

202
00:14:56,015 --> 00:14:57,975
Things aren't always what they seem.

203
00:14:58,518 --> 00:15:01,352
I'm sure Do Hee is the one who messed up.

204
00:15:01,382 --> 00:15:02,654
You think so?

205
00:15:10,486 --> 00:15:14,677
I'm sorry. I was wrong, Ji Ni.

206
00:15:15,487 --> 00:15:17,596
Please don't do this.

207
00:15:31,700 --> 00:15:32,918
Yes?

208
00:15:34,407 --> 00:15:36,217
Are you still sitting like this?

209
00:15:36,290 --> 00:15:38,350
I was just going to shower.

210
00:15:39,193 --> 00:15:40,368
You...

211
00:15:40,785 --> 00:15:42,526
had a fight with Do Hee, right?

212
00:15:43,025 --> 00:15:44,462
No. Don't worry about it.

213
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:46,199
How can I not worry?

214
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:49,700
Do Hee was walking on eggshells
around you.

215
00:15:49,886 --> 00:15:52,085
She must've done something wrong.

216
00:15:52,447 --> 00:15:54,570
But don't be too harsh with her.

217
00:15:54,913 --> 00:15:56,449
You shouldn't treat a woman that way.

218
00:15:56,473 --> 00:15:57,726
Am I that harsh?

219
00:15:57,751 --> 00:15:58,932
You didn't know?

220
00:15:58,993 --> 00:16:01,186
You're exactly like your father.

221
00:16:01,759 --> 00:16:04,640
You're so sweet until
something rubs you the wrong way.

222
00:16:04,664 --> 00:16:06,664
Then you suddenly go cold.

223
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:08,431
That's mean. Fix it.

224
00:16:09,420 --> 00:16:11,347
How's your hand?

225
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:15,967
Didn't you play the piano
for too long today?

226
00:16:16,050 --> 00:16:18,959
I'm fine. I couldn't even play that hard.

227
00:16:24,456 --> 00:16:26,470
You should be nicer to Do Hee.

228
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:28,046
Don't be so harsh with her.

229
00:16:29,267 --> 00:16:33,258
Marriage isn't about personal taste.
It's about the family you marry into.

230
00:16:33,282 --> 00:16:34,354
Take today, for example.

231
00:16:34,386 --> 00:16:36,392
She knew every minister there.

232
00:16:36,793 --> 00:16:39,392
Those connections will all benefit you.

233
00:16:39,686 --> 00:16:41,887
- They're the perfect in-laws.
- That's not why...

234
00:16:41,911 --> 00:16:43,160
I'm dating Do Hee.

235
00:16:43,184 --> 00:16:44,563
Then why are you with her?

236
00:16:46,050 --> 00:16:48,070
Besides being pretty and kind.

237
00:16:48,597 --> 00:16:51,259
- What else do you like about her?
- Mom, seriously.

238
00:16:53,032 --> 00:16:56,832
I saved her when some kids
bullied her at school in England.

239
00:16:58,032 --> 00:17:00,136
She was bullied
when she first studied abroad.

240
00:17:00,161 --> 00:17:03,239
I can't believe someone like her
was the one being bullied.

241
00:17:04,587 --> 00:17:05,805
See?

242
00:17:06,120 --> 00:17:09,653
Do Hee may seem tough,
but she's soft-hearted.

243
00:17:09,912 --> 00:17:11,399
Treat her well!

244
00:17:11,613 --> 00:17:14,160
Don't let someone like her
slip through your fingers!

245
00:17:15,270 --> 00:17:16,270
Get some rest.

246
00:17:17,313 --> 00:17:18,447
Okay.

247
00:17:26,625 --> 00:17:29,147
(Haemyeong University Hospital,
Funeral Hall)

248
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:44,653
I'm not going to the crematorium.

249
00:17:44,706 --> 00:17:46,568
I'll go straight to the tree burial site.

250
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:49,318
Show them that precious family register
of yours,

251
00:17:49,356 --> 00:17:50,932
and make sure he's cremated properly.

252
00:17:51,199 --> 00:17:52,199
Okay.

253
00:17:53,667 --> 00:17:56,739
We'll come straight over
once the hearse leaves.

254
00:17:56,839 --> 00:18:00,173
Wait at the tree burial site
and take care of the rest.

255
00:18:00,203 --> 00:18:01,293
Okay.

256
00:18:02,737 --> 00:18:03,737
Well...

257
00:18:05,173 --> 00:18:08,359
You kept everything in order
right to the very end.

258
00:18:08,956 --> 00:18:10,029
Thank you.

259
00:18:11,639 --> 00:18:14,430
Go home and get some sleep,
then come to the tree burial site.

260
00:18:14,459 --> 00:18:16,355
Tonight is my last night with dad.

261
00:18:16,420 --> 00:18:18,395
I'll stay here tonight,
then go to the crematorium.

262
00:18:18,523 --> 00:18:19,814
I can come too, right?

263
00:18:22,926 --> 00:18:24,218
You're so stubborn.

264
00:18:26,846 --> 00:18:28,547
Do whatever you want. I'm leaving.

265
00:18:37,939 --> 00:18:40,015
She and her father seemed very close.

266
00:18:40,780 --> 00:18:42,647
You should head home too
and return at dawn.

267
00:18:42,813 --> 00:18:45,135
Doesn't it bother you?
Are you really okay?

268
00:18:45,160 --> 00:18:46,875
What do you expect me to say?

269
00:18:46,948 --> 00:18:48,528
I'm fine.

270
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:50,278
I feel bad for mom and Seung Woo.

271
00:18:50,303 --> 00:18:52,482
You always say you're fine.

272
00:18:53,466 --> 00:18:55,602
At least he was good
to one of his families.

273
00:18:55,666 --> 00:18:58,993
My husband is such a class act.

274
00:19:00,120 --> 00:19:01,774
Will you go home or sleep here?

275
00:19:02,798 --> 00:19:04,031
I'll sleep here.

276
00:19:04,056 --> 00:19:05,718
It's harder to come back at dawn.

277
00:19:13,553 --> 00:19:14,598
What is it?

278
00:19:14,622 --> 00:19:17,325
Nothing. My husband's just so amazing.

279
00:19:17,560 --> 00:19:19,893
O Reum will grow up...

280
00:19:19,917 --> 00:19:21,997
to be as big-hearted as you, right?

281
00:19:40,439 --> 00:19:42,286
Go inside and get some rest.

282
00:19:43,732 --> 00:19:45,367
Did O Reum go home?

283
00:19:45,925 --> 00:19:46,925
No.

284
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:48,900
Are you going to stay here?

285
00:19:49,436 --> 00:19:50,436
Yes.

286
00:19:50,766 --> 00:19:52,213
Don't worry about me.

287
00:20:17,366 --> 00:20:19,893
Why are you still awake?

288
00:20:20,374 --> 00:20:21,606
What's this?

289
00:20:23,226 --> 00:20:25,611
It's a Vietnamese snack called Bongao.

290
00:20:25,780 --> 00:20:28,630
You don't give these to just anyone.
What brought this on?

291
00:20:30,034 --> 00:20:31,358
Thank you.

292
00:20:32,394 --> 00:20:34,610
- Want to draw?
- I want to draw.

293
00:20:34,666 --> 00:20:36,208
Okay. Come here.

294
00:20:42,210 --> 00:20:43,950
You should be sleeping.

295
00:20:45,786 --> 00:20:48,709
I'll let you know
when he gets sleepy after playing a bit.

296
00:20:49,010 --> 00:20:51,206
Okay. Thank you.

297
00:20:59,298 --> 00:21:00,885
You drew this really well.

298
00:21:01,470 --> 00:21:03,045
What did you draw here?

299
00:21:04,010 --> 00:21:05,436
A beautiful sun.

300
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:07,602
"A beautiful sun!"

301
00:21:11,740 --> 00:21:12,953
Were you there?

302
00:21:13,238 --> 00:21:14,322
Why didn't you come inside?

303
00:21:14,370 --> 00:21:16,427
He said he didn't come in
because he might kill someone.

304
00:21:16,953 --> 00:21:19,638
Uncle, you sure have a lot of energy.

305
00:21:19,678 --> 00:21:20,887
But that's not what he meant.

306
00:21:20,903 --> 00:21:23,112
He wasn't saying he'd kill that woman.

307
00:21:24,414 --> 00:21:28,590
- You said you were going to sleep.
- So what? We're family.

308
00:21:29,140 --> 00:21:32,197
He wants to kill Yeong Ju. Not that woman.

309
00:21:32,399 --> 00:21:35,066
Because I said she stayed with him
until he passed away.

310
00:21:35,474 --> 00:21:38,222
What an idiot! She's always been one.

311
00:21:38,318 --> 00:21:40,685
I'm that idiot's son.

312
00:21:40,994 --> 00:21:43,286
I understand how you feel,

313
00:21:43,338 --> 00:21:45,294
but calling my mom an idiot
in front of her son...

314
00:21:46,550 --> 00:21:48,523
You're my nephew.

315
00:21:48,798 --> 00:21:51,448
I lived with your mom long before you did.

316
00:21:51,510 --> 00:21:53,814
I told her from the start
not to marry him.

317
00:21:53,860 --> 00:21:56,387
He was the type of man
who only said sweet things...

318
00:21:56,430 --> 00:21:58,118
and won people over
with that charming smile.

319
00:21:58,170 --> 00:22:00,103
Even after I warned her,
she fell for him completely...

320
00:22:00,450 --> 00:22:02,443
and suddenly got pregnant with Seung Hyun.

321
00:22:02,622 --> 00:22:03,767
Seriously!

322
00:22:03,768 --> 00:22:05,870
Your uncle was pretty sweet.

323
00:22:05,920 --> 00:22:08,556
Even I lose my mind sometimes.

324
00:22:09,154 --> 00:22:11,000
He was thoughtful and affectionate.

325
00:22:11,920 --> 00:22:13,568
That's what everyone says,

326
00:22:13,994 --> 00:22:16,216
but I never experienced it.

327
00:22:18,050 --> 00:22:21,062
- You should go inside.
- Okay.

328
00:22:21,520 --> 00:22:24,792
Let me know if you need anything.

329
00:22:31,162 --> 00:22:32,546
Don't mind it.

330
00:22:33,466 --> 00:22:34,770
I don't.

331
00:22:35,380 --> 00:22:37,103
But I'm curious.

332
00:22:37,702 --> 00:22:40,358
What was so sweet about him?

333
00:22:40,900 --> 00:22:42,236
To my brother and me,

334
00:22:42,470 --> 00:22:46,326
we only ever saw his cold back
walking out the door every day.

335
00:22:46,619 --> 00:22:48,126
That bastard.

336
00:22:48,214 --> 00:22:49,974
He should've suffered more before dying.

337
00:22:50,680 --> 00:22:52,240
But I heard he apologized.

338
00:22:52,290 --> 00:22:54,690
He got on his knees a few days
before he left.

339
00:22:54,742 --> 00:22:57,377
He must've worn his knees out.

340
00:22:57,494 --> 00:23:00,290
He begged your grandfather
to let him marry,

341
00:23:00,338 --> 00:23:03,277
then got on his knees again
to ask for a divorce.

342
00:23:03,734 --> 00:23:05,469
What's so special about his knees?

343
00:23:07,210 --> 00:23:10,170
Yes. It all feels so hollow.

344
00:23:10,210 --> 00:23:11,920
That's why I didn't go
into the funeral hall.

345
00:23:11,953 --> 00:23:13,906
Watching you guys like this pisses me off.

346
00:23:13,960 --> 00:23:16,145
And I'd have to see that woman too.

347
00:23:16,399 --> 00:23:17,822
I can't handle that.

348
00:23:17,860 --> 00:23:20,754
Seung Hyun seems fine though.
Like nothing bothers him.

349
00:23:21,150 --> 00:23:23,110
Seung Hyun's something else.

350
00:23:23,962 --> 00:23:26,323
Honestly, he's the scariest one.

351
00:23:29,080 --> 00:23:30,253
You're right.

352
00:23:30,270 --> 00:23:35,331
When mom opposed him marrying Mai,
he settled it in one go.

353
00:23:35,514 --> 00:23:37,118
He's a strange guy.

354
00:23:37,146 --> 00:23:39,324
Is she doing well? Her name is Mai, right?

355
00:23:39,966 --> 00:23:42,034
She's like the Joan of Arc of our family.

356
00:23:42,070 --> 00:23:46,251
Her Korean's so good,
none of us can beat her.

357
00:23:48,606 --> 00:23:51,270
(Haemyeong University Hospital,
Funeral Hall)

358
00:24:19,606 --> 00:24:21,911
You could at least turn off the AC
before sleeping.

359
00:25:43,336 --> 00:25:44,520
Yes, Aunt.

360
00:25:46,174 --> 00:25:47,565
She must've gone too.

361
00:25:48,031 --> 00:25:50,407
She's probably following them
from somewhere out of sight.

362
00:25:50,410 --> 00:25:53,898
She slept there for the past two nights,

363
00:25:53,934 --> 00:25:57,102
grieving for her dad
more than anyone else...

364
00:25:58,394 --> 00:26:01,630
Imagine how hurt he'd be if he knew.

365
00:26:02,814 --> 00:26:05,353
He always walked hand in hand with her,

366
00:26:05,970 --> 00:26:07,601
so this breaks my heart.

367
00:26:10,514 --> 00:26:11,702
Aunt.

368
00:26:14,786 --> 00:26:17,482
I couldn't even be with him
in his final moments.

369
00:26:17,823 --> 00:26:20,347
His legal wife was there instead.

370
00:26:25,250 --> 00:26:28,463
I'm not crying. I'm not the type to cry.

371
00:26:28,742 --> 00:26:29,802
Okay.

372
00:26:30,870 --> 00:26:33,780
Don't go to the tree burial site.
The heat will be too much for you.

373
00:26:34,910 --> 00:26:36,102
Okay.

374
00:26:45,874 --> 00:26:48,544
Honey, do you know something?

375
00:26:50,086 --> 00:26:52,371
Loving you...

376
00:26:54,218 --> 00:26:55,852
was never easy.

377
00:26:57,574 --> 00:26:59,302
I didn't want to feel humiliated,

378
00:26:59,914 --> 00:27:04,685
so I fought every day to seem fine.

379
00:27:09,250 --> 00:27:11,092
But now, it's all over.

380
00:27:15,002 --> 00:27:17,147
You can be at peace now.

381
00:27:21,058 --> 00:27:22,934
You tried so hard...

382
00:27:23,510 --> 00:27:25,005
to stay with me...

383
00:27:26,090 --> 00:27:27,590
Thank you so much.

384
00:27:29,338 --> 00:27:30,698
Honey.

385
00:27:32,490 --> 00:27:34,472
I miss you so much.

386
00:28:17,966 --> 00:28:21,250
(Family Register)

387
00:28:21,482 --> 00:28:24,698
I buried all my resentment
under that tree and came back.

388
00:28:24,733 --> 00:28:27,109
- I'm still single.
- Really?

389
00:28:27,160 --> 00:28:29,462
The way she treats you is so different
from her paintings. It's strange.

390
00:28:29,510 --> 00:28:31,014
Do we need to divide the house?

391
00:28:31,058 --> 00:28:32,938
That paper will be the death of me.

392
00:28:32,980 --> 00:28:34,614
He apologized to me before he died.

393
00:28:34,660 --> 00:28:35,718
I was there when he took his last breath.

394
00:28:35,760 --> 00:28:37,386
Do you really want to get a ring
with that money?

395
00:28:37,412 --> 00:28:39,218
- What's the total?
- One hundred twenty thousand dollars!

396
00:28:44,099 --> 00:28:46,196
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
